06/12/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The senior partners in Romania's ruling coalition -- the National Liberal Party (PNL) and the Democratic Party -- named replacements Tuesday (December 5th) for three vacant cabinet positions. 
PNL general secretary Dan Motreanu was nominated as agriculture minister, replacing Gheorghe Flutur. 
PNL Senator Varujan Vosganian, who recently withdrew his nomination as Romania's EU Commissioner, was nominated to replace Gheorghe Pogea as a deputy prime minister, and Democrat Mircea Toader, current state secretary at the Ministry of Administration and Interior, was named minister of economy and trade. 
Parliament is expected to vote on the shuffle next week. 
(Adevarul, Cotidianul, Ziua - 06/12/06; Rompres, Mediafax - 05/12/06)
